Something about its conical shape and wireframe that I thought I could use. I toyed back and forth for a while to no avail looking for something until I noticed it resembled a trumpet or horn, then I remembered the TV show Time Trumpet and so the two ideas collided to give you the final product. A spaceman playing a trumpet that can make sound travel through time and space. Thats make sense right? name: My Darling, We Made It
description: This illustration is homage of the captivating & famous scene when Gene Kelly has fallen in love and sang in the rain. As you guessed, ‘Singin’ in the Rain’ is one of my favourite feel-good movie. I expressed these emotions in an illustration. It’s natural to feel vulnerable under beady eyes but once in awhile, thrown caution to the wind. Knowing you are cherished is the beauty of being alive.
